  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To start, chop up a garlic clove and whack into a pan with a glug of olive oil, your plant-based mince, 1 tsp sugar, 1 tsp smoked paprika and 1 tsp cinnamon. Break up and fry until crispy. Set aside and cover with foil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Next, finely chop your onion and 2 garlic cloves. Heat a glug of oil and fry the onion and garlic for 5 minutes."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When soft, add 2 tsp paprika, 1 tsp cinnamon, 1 tsp sugar, a sprinkle of salt and your cumin. Mix together."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Next, toss in your chickpeas with their water and chopped tomatoes and mix. Then add your stock cubes and mix until fully dissolved."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your coriander, add to the tomato mix (saving some for a garnish) then set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a separate bowl, mix together your tahini, lemon juice, glug of oil, cup of water, salt and pepper. Keep stirring until you have a thick paste and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once finished, its time to plate up. Spoon your stew into 4 bowls and drizzle with your tahini paste. Sprinkle over your crispy mince (re-heating in a pan if required) and any leftover coriander leaves then tuck in!"
    }
  ],
